originalText.text: Matilda has been a huge help to me over the years as I have struggled with depression.  She truly cared about my struggles and was a very compassionate and emphatic listener.  She understands mental illness and the difficulties of living with depression and was able to make suggestions that helped me deal with the depression.  She also is familiar with many outside resources (books, podcasts, etc.) that helped me in my journey with depression.  Whenever I needed her support and encouragement, she was always available and willing to schedule a time to talk.  I highly recommend Matilda--she made me feel very comfortable as I discussed my concerns with her and she was very easy to open up to.  Matilda understands that life is not easy and many times we just need someone who really listens and cares to help us navigate through whatever it is we may be struggling with (family or friend issues, difficult relationships at home or work, or difficult life events, for example).  Additionally, Matilda is very open minded and supportive of the LGBTQ community, which I believe is very positive.  I also liked very much that her fees are extremely reasonable because I could not afford the higher fees that clinical therapists are charging.  I totally trust her wisdom and life knowledge and know I can count on Matilda to help me with any concerns/difficulties as they arise on life's journey.

originalText.text: When I reached out to Matilda, I was drowning in a sea of confusion, hurt, stress, and pain. After the first few minutes of talking with her, I immediately felt calmer. Matilda is real. She has walked the walk and knows how it feels when life seems bigger than you. Her emotional intelligence guided me through my struggles but gave me the power to manage them.
